=head1 DESCRIPTION

The ID for the rule type, which is made up of the combined values for
category, owner, provider, and version. For more information about
conditions, see Stage conditions
(https://docs.aws.amazon.com/codepipeline/latest/userguide/stage-conditions.html).
For more information about rules, see the CodePipeline rule reference
(https://docs.aws.amazon.com/codepipeline/latest/userguide/rule-reference.html).

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 B<REQUIRED> Category => Str

A category defines what kind of rule can be run in the stage, and
constrains the provider type for the rule. The valid category is
C<Rule>.


=head2 Owner => Str

The creator of the rule being called. The valid value for the C<Owner>
field in the rule category is C<AWS>.


=head2 B<REQUIRED> Provider => Str

The rule provider, such as the C<DeploymentWindow> rule. For a list of
rule provider names, see the rules listed in the CodePipeline rule
reference
(https://docs.aws.amazon.com/codepipeline/latest/userguide/rule-reference.html).


=head2 Version => Str

A string that describes the rule version.



